{"id":"chozeba","term":"Chozeba","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>(<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 4:22\">1 Chr. 4:22</a>), the same as Chezib and Achzib, a place in the lowlands of Judah (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 38:5\">Gen. 38:5</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Joshua 15:44\">Josh. 15:44</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Chronicles 4:22","Genesis 38:5","Joshua 15:44"]}